.hero--fifth
  .hero__body--h100
    .hero__body__inner
      .hero__heading
        img.space--bottom-5.wow.fadeIn data-wow-offset="250" src="/images/track.png" alt="Track content"
        h2
          | Track
      .hero__text.space--bottom-8
        p
          | The Reader tracks users' reading behavior and allows partners to apply some restrictions based on it.
      .hero__body__ruler.space--bottom-8
      .wrap
        .grid--center
          .grid__item.desk-6-12
            p.beta.align--center
              | How do we count characters?
            .hero__text
              ul
                li.align--center
                  | 1. The Reader counts the visible characters on the page;
                li.align--center
                  | 2. it monitors the user's time spent on each page;
                li.align--center
                  | 3. after a calculated time, the page is considered to have been read;
                li.align--center
                  | 4. a user-related log is written with the position in the book and the number of characters read. 
          .grid__item.desk-6-12
            p.beta.align--center
              | How do we measure image sizes?
            .hero__text
              ul
                li.align--center
                  | 1. the character count includes stats for images;
                li.align--center
                  | 2. an image is considered to be equal to a number of characters based on its dimensions (H * W * X multiplication factor);
                li.align--center
                  | 3. the 'multiplication factor' is configurable per partner/book, and defaults to 0.001.
